Author: Zahn
Zahn: *Gesch. d. NT. Kan.* ii. p. 657; Zahn's conjecture is that a. θαμβηβεὶς b. that θαμβηβεὶς is a mistranslation of a Hebrew/Aramaic word also meaning θορυβηθείς and thus συντετριμμένης would be the right term; howver θαμβηθείς appears in the pap. and so this further conjecture is disproved.

Author: Graefe
Bordeline: Pap. has ἀκωκήν corrected to κορώνην (i.e. κολώνην) which is corrected to ἀκωκήν (which is from the end of 394).
